                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1388a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. For General Russell:</p>
                <p>Bids for loans opened this afternoon. National City Company bid 92.137; Lee,
                    Higginson and Company bid 90.427 and Speyer and Blair bid 88.03125. Loan was
                    awarded to National City. Please have figures kept strictly confidential as
                    details will not be made public for the present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
